cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it deals with network function virtualization and OpenFlow enabled cloud networks. It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses security violations that can occur due to inefficient deployment of network functions. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it proposes a solution for improving SFC performance through network function parallelism. It may also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it utilizes the SDN framework for managing the OpenStack cloud network. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it utilizes the DPDK platform for experimental analysis.
